data.description: Covers the graphs, properties and geometric significance of trigonometric functions of a real variable. data.description: Examines issues related to global agriculture and healthy sustainable development. Using a regional approach and focusing on crops and livestock case studies, students will learn the interdependence between US agriculture and agriculture in emerging economies. Some topics covered include population and food, immigration, the environment; crop and livestock agriculture; global trade; sustainability; and the role of women in agriculture and the role of dairy products in a healthy diet.
data.title: INTERNATIONAL FIELD STUDY IN ANIMAL AGRICULTURE AND SUSTAINABLE DEVELOPMENT

data.description: Examines issues related to global agriculture and healthy sustainable development. Dissections of earthworm, freshwater mussel, squid, sea star, and rat aid the study of these general principles.
